{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"tore-dryad-snout","description":"# scripts/probe-rebar.sh has 3 stale assertions vs the current engine\n\n## What\nThe release smoke probe reports 3 failures that are NOT engine defects — the probe\nscript tests behavior the engine intentionally changed. Surfaced during the 0.6.0\nrelease smoke test (138 passed, 3 failed).\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n1. Init an isolated store with a current rebar build.\n2. `REBAR_ROOT=<store> PROBE_LIVE=1 bash scripts/probe-rebar.sh`.\n3. Observe 3 failures unrelated to engine correctness.\n\nExpected: probe asserts only current, supported behavior (0 spurious failures).\nActual: 3 failures from stale expectations.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `scripts/probe-rebar.sh` line ~146: stop using removed `edit --tags`; use\n      `--set-tags`/`--add-tag`/`--remove-tag` (per CLAUDE.md tag-delta surface).\n- [ ] Line ~147 priority assertion passes once the edit command no longer errors.\n- [ ] Line ~276 keyset assertion accounts for `show` including `comments`+`description`\n      that `list` omits by design (don't assert identical key sets).\n- [ ] Full probe prints `N passed, 0 failed` against the current engine.","id":"08ce-0e74-07f6-414e","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"probe-rebar.sh: 3 stale assertions (edit --tags removed; show/list keyset)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782767103662838001,"uuid":"81292f81-d287-47d4-9313-c7447b03d860"}